    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-09-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <head>No. 24.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Clapp</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos
                                        Ayres</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 12,
                                    1872</date>. (Received October 22.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that no
                            perceptible change has taken place in the condition of affairs as
                            respects the difficulty between the Argentine Republic and Brazil.
                            Reports as to the success of the mission of General Mitre are
                            conflicting.</p>
                <p>I stated in a former dispatch that a portion of the Grand Chaco, about
                            which more than any other matter this trouble with Brazil has arisen, is
                            claimed by the republic of Bolivia. Señor R. Cordona has lately arrived
                            at this capital, as special envoy from Bolivia, for the settlement of
                            this question.</p>
                <p>* * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>DEXTER E. CLAPP.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
